The provenance, privacy, and licensing posture of this investigation's record.

## Repository posture

**Artifact policy:** `{{artifact_policy}}`

{{#if private_archive}}
This is an **always-private archive**. The repo is the durable backup for scarce
inputs; it deliberately commits proprietary artifacts, evidence (which may carry
identifying detail — serial numbers, photos, labels), and all documentation. Only
reproducible blobs (large images/dumps) are git-ignored.

**Do not push this repo to a shared or public remote.** That is the single most
consequential mistake available here. There is no public-safe subset; treat the
whole repo as private.
{{/if}}
{{#if public_writeup}}
This investigation is intended to be **publishable**. No proprietary blobs are
committed — artifacts are referenced, not stored. Before making the repo public,
sweep `evidence/` and the docs for anything identifying or proprietary that
shouldn't be public.
{{/if}}
{{#if no_artifacts}}
No artifact-storage machinery is configured. Keep proprietary or identifying
material out of the repo.
{{/if}}

## Third-party terms

The project's [LICENSE](../LICENSE) (`{{license_spdx}}`) covers **only** the
original written record and any scripts authored here. It does **not** relicense
third-party artifacts the repo references or stores — those keep their own terms.
When in doubt, note the artifact's origin and terms in its manifest.

